{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> συνοικ-ίζω</b>, <br /> <i>future</i> <i>Attic dialect</i> <b>-ιῶ</b>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Diodorus Siculus Historicus 2.6 \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]: <i>perfect</i> <b>-ῴκικα</b>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC-1st c.AD: Strabo Geographus 12.3.10 \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]:— <b>make to live with</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 19.34, uncertain reading in Ps.- 5th c.BC: Epicharmus Comicus 298 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; σ. τινὶ τὴν θυγατέρα <b>to give</b> him one's daughter <b>in marriage</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.121.ζ᾽,compare “PEnteux.” 22.8 (3rd c.BC), 1st c.BC: Diodorus Siculus Historicus 2.6; σ. νύμφας νυμφίοις 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 546d, compare “Sph.” 242d; ἐμὲ.. εὐνὴν Ἡρακλεῖ συνοικίσας 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hercules Furens” 68 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; rarely with the reverse <i>construction</i>, τοὺς δούλους ταῖς τῶν δεσποτῶν γυναιξὶ σ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 16.13.1. \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>combine</b> or <b>join in one city</b>, μὴ Τροίαν ἀθροίσῃ καὶ ξυνοικίσῃ πάλιν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hecuba” 1139 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>unite into a city-state</b>, ἐς τὴν νῦν πόλιν οὖσαν ξ. πάντας [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.15; Θησεὺς.. τὰς δώο̄εκα πόλεις εἰς τὸ αὐτὸ συνῴκισεν “Marm.Par.” 35 (compare συνοίκια); ξ. τὴν Λέσβον ἐς τὴν Μυτιλήνην 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 3.2; Ἐρέτρια συνῴκισε τὰς περὶ Παλλήνην πόλεις 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Fragmenta” 603:\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] —<i>passive</i>, ξυνοικισθείσης πόλεως a city <b>having been regularly formed</b>, opposed to κατὰ κώμας οἰκίζεσθαι, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.10, compare 2.16, 3.93; ἐκ μικρῶν πόλεων συνοικισθέντες 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Respublica Atheniensium” 2.2; Χαλκιδέων εἰς ἓν συνῳκισμένων 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 19.263; σ. κατὰ πόλεις 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 15.82 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐκ τῶν τυχόντων ἀνθρώπων σ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Lycurgus Orator 62. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> <b>unite in one building,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Zenon Papyri Michegan 84.9 (_passive_, 3rd c.BC). \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <b>join in peopling</b> or <b>colonizing</b> a country, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.24 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τισι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 6.5. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__IV</b></Level2> generally, <b>unite, associate</b>, οἵῳ με δαίμων φιλοσόφῳ συνῴκισεν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Theognetus Comicus 1.6; λιμὸν σ. τινί 4th c.AD: Alciphro Epistolographus 1.20; ἀλλοτρίῳ δαίμονι συνοικιζομένους 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Coriolanus” 13. \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G9332","accentedUnicode":"συνοικίζω","shortDef":"to live together","mediumDef":"to live together","stepGloss":"to live together","stepTransliteration":"sunoikizō","_step_Type":"verb"}]}